# Update Documentation

When asked to update documentation after code changes, read and follow the skill at `docs/skills/update-docs.md`.

Key points:
- Input is optional. If no git reference or description is given, default to uncommitted changes (`HEAD`).
- Map changed source files to affected docs using `docs/BOOKMARKS.md` as the index.
- A code change can affect multiple doc types — check overview docs, guides, READMEs, ADRs, and agent rules.
- Update only the affected sections; do not rewrite unaffected content.
- Update the `Last Updated` date if the doc uses one.
- Show a summary of proposed changes before writing.
